g in the docstring is unusual, but the most straightforward approach is to treat the input `payload` as a JWT token string and decode it using the `jwt` library, returning the decoded content as a dictionary.\n\nSince no secret key is provided as a parameter, I'll decode without signature verification using `options={\"verify_signature\": False}`. This is appropriate when the goal is simply to extract and read the token's claims rather than validate its authenticity.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4676,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4676},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6aae3af-0fa4-4eba-8d00-83c702689df7","uuid":"56285349-0747-4e44-b55e-3cea49beca3b","request_id":"req_011CbdQCzGVRBoCH6AXa6P3v"}
